{"id": "duc04-testb-6:7#23", "contents": "During his visit, Chung is expected to finalize details of Hyundai's plan to start sightseeing tours of Diamond Mountain, a scenic mountain in the North. The tours, initially scheduled to begin in September, have been delayed due to various issues. Hyundai aims to send up to 2,000 tourists a week for four-day tours of Diamond Mountain on the North's east coast, starting in November. The two Koreas have a long history of animosity and distrust, having been separated into the communist North and the capitalist South in 1945, and fighting a three-year war in the early 1950s."}
